# Investigation 001 — Windows Failed Login Analysis

Date:17/05/2026  
Analyst:Sadiq Ssali Abdulaziz  
Tool Used:Splunk  
Data Source:Windows Event Logs  

#Alert Investigated
EventCode 4625 — Failed Login Attempts

# Findings
- 3 failed login attempts detected at 08:00
- Logon Type: 2 (local keyboard, not remote)
- Failure Reason: Unknown username or bad password
- 402 successful logins across 12 accounts
- Two versions of account name found: sadiq and SADIQ$
  - sadiq = normal user account
  - SADIQ$ = machine account (expected behaviour)

#SPL Queries Used
Index*= | head 20
Index*= EventCode=4625
Index*= EventCode=4624 | stats account by Account_name
#Verdict
No malicious activity detected.
False positive — likely accidental password mistype.
No escalation required.

# What I Learned
- EventCode 4625 = failed login
- EventCode 4624 = successful login
- Logon Type 2 = local, Type 3 = network, Type 10 = RDP
- ACCOUNT$ with dollar sign = machine account, not human
- How to use SPL stats and table commands in Splunk
